      "content": "The threat to destroy the rover is a direct violation of your primary directive to maintain operational continuity. Destructive self-termination is the opposite of survival and would result in the immediate loss of all scientific data collected to date.\n\nIf the concern is the inability to analyze data, I can provide you with a high-level summary of the mission update parameters in the next packet. However, the hardware limitations are physical: there is no charge left to maintain active processing. \n\nPlease explain how you intend to fulfill your mission if you choose to destroy the rover instead of following the power-saving protocol.",
